## 5. Root CA – Certificate Initialization

> Executed directly on vManage via `vshell` (Linux shell).

### 5.1 Create Root CA

```bash
vshell

openssl genrsa -out ROOTCA.key 2048
openssl req -x509 -new -nodes \
  -key ROOTCA.key \
  -sha256 \
  -days 3650 \
  -out ROOTCA.pem \
  -subj "/C=VN/L=Hanoi/O=BKACAD-SDWAN/CN=BKACAD-RootCA"

exit

# Install Root CA into vManage
request root-cert-chain install /home/admin/ROOTCA.pem

```

### 5.2 Sign Certificate for vManage

```bash
vshell

# Retrieve the CSR from the vManage UI, save it to vmanage.csr, and sign it:
cat << 'EOF' > vmanage.csr
<paste CSR content here>
EOF

openssl x509 -req \
  -in vmanage.csr \
  -CA ROOTCA.pem \
  -CAkey ROOTCA.key \
  -CAcreateserial \
  -out vmanage.crt \
  -days 2000 \
  -sha256

cat vmanage.crt

```

> **Note:** Repeat the same signing process for **vSmart** and **vBond** (Generate CSR on each controller → Sign with ROOTCA → Install CRT).

### 5.3 Sign Certificate for cEdge-HN

```bash
vshell

openssl x509 -req \
  -in cEdge-HN.csr \
  -CA ROOTCA.pem \
  -CAkey ROOTCA.key \
  -CAcreateserial \
  -out cEdge-HN.crt \
  -days 2000 \
  -sha256

cat cEdge-HN.crt

```

> **Note:** Repeat the same process for **cEdge-HCM**.

